Package: poppr
Type: Package
Title: an R package for genetic analysis of populations with mixed
    reproduction
Version: 1.0.3
Date: 2013-08-21
Author: Zhian N. Kamvar <kamvarz@science.oregonstate.edu>, Javier F. Tabima
    <tabimaj@onid.orst.edu>, Niklaus J. Grunwald
    <grunwaln@science.oregonstate.edu>
Maintainer: Zhian N. Kamvar <kamvarz@science.oregonstate.edu>
URL: http://cran.r-project.org/package=poppr,
    http://grunwaldlab.cgrb.oregonstate.edu/poppr-r-package-population-genetics
Description: Population genetic analyses for hierarchical analysis of partially
    clonal populations built upon the architecture of the adegenet package.
Depends:
    R (>= 2.15.1),
    adegenet,
    pegas,
    vegan
Imports:
    adegenet,
    pegas,
    vegan,
    ggplot2,
    phangorn,
    ape,
    igraph
License: GPL-2
Collate:
    'Index_calculations.r'
    'file_handling.r'
    'sample_schemes.r'
    'visualizations.r'
    'mlg.r'
    'bruvo.r'
    'data_subset.r'
    'internal.r'
    'sandbox.r'
    'distances.r'
